Debugging c++ programs 


https://cets.seas.upenn.edu/answers/gcc.html
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/gdb-step-by-step-introduction/


do not forget when compiling c++ files to put -g for debugging purposes


Commands :

watch variable // watch variable
continue c
print variable  p var // print stored variable
next  n // step
run  r // run program
layout next // show source code
break main, line, function_name b main  // make a break point


example of debugging command sequence

gdb a.out
layout next
b main
r
n
c
watch I
print var
quit

